cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.DB, cs.SE, cs.CY 

The paper focuses on enhancing security against insider attacks in services that manage sensitive data, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The use of autonomous data management and secure hardware also involves distributed computing (cs.DC) and database systems (cs.DB). The implementation and management of the system involves software engineering (cs.SE) and the use of a distributed ledger involves cryptography (cs.CY).
